title: Classic Green Bean Casserole
description: It's the dish everyone's expecting on the holidays, but it's so easy to make, you can serve it any day. What makes our green bean casserole so good?  A secret ingredient. Cream of mushroom soup.

title: Broccoli Rice Casserole
description: What makes this quick-cooking side dish really tasty is coating the broccoli and rice in a creamy cheese sauce. Yum.

title: Squash Casserole
description: This creamy, crowd-pleasing side dish features summer squash, carrots, stuffing mix and cheese baked in a creamy sauce. Crispy on top and creamy in the center, it's a winner on any menu.

title: Slow Cooker Scalloped Potatoes
description: Layered potatoes and onion are topped with a creamy mixture featuring Cheddar cheese soup, milk, Parmesan, Cheddar cheese and are then slow cooked to perfection. They're so good you'll never make scalloped potatoes any other way!

title: Cheddar Potato Casserole
description: Savory mashed potatoes are laced with a cheddar cheese sauce, sour cream and green onion. Baked to a golden turn, this dish is a real crowd pleaser.

title: Baked Macaroni & Cheese
description: This extra-easy version of a classic casserole is homey, cheesy and topped with crunchy bread crumbs to make it even better.

title: Baked Ziti
description: Short tube-shaped pasta tossed with seasoned tomato sauce, mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses is baked in a casserole until bubbling.

title: 3-Cheese Pasta Bake
description: This mouthwatering version of baked macaroni and cheese is ready in just 40 minutes and features our secret ingredient cream of mushroom soup. Try it as a side dish too!

title: Miracle Lasagna
description: Traditional, full-flavored lasagna is layered together in just minutes with pasta sauce, noodles, and three cheeses.

title: Broccoli Cheddar Rice
description: Looking for a tasty side to feed a hungry crowd? Sawtayed broccoli, onion and garlic combine with Cheddar cheese soup, milk, brown rice and Parmesan cheese. Baked until hot and bubbling, this fabulous casserole is chock full of flavor and ready in just 1 hour!

title: Ranchero Macaroni Bake
description: This tasty twist on classic mac and cheese uses picante sauce and crushed tortilla chips to kick-up the flavor, and make a good thing even better!

title: Crowd-Pleasing Vegetable Casserole
description: Everyone will eat and enjoy their vegetables when this casserole is served. You can use your favorite frozen vegetable mixture to suit your family's tastes. And it's ready in under 45 minutes.

title: Broccoli & Noodles Supreme
description: The trick to this simply delicious recipe is that the broccoli and noodles cook together...mixed with a creamy, cheesy sauce, this 35-minute dish is really good!

title: Creamy Poblano Mac & Cheese
description: Mac & cheese goes from ordinary to extraordinary with the addition of sawtayed fresh vegetables and creamy poblano & queso soup. This crowd pleasing casserole is incredibly good, easy to prepare and sure to earn rave reviews!

title: Quick Quesadillas
description: These quick cooking quesadillas are loaded with cheese, salsa and green onions and are perfect for those busy weeknights when you don't have a lot of time. They're easy, kid-friendly and just plain good!

title: Swiss Vegetable Casserole
description: Served hot and bubbly from the oven, this colorful and cheese-topped veggie casserole is good enough to steal the limelight from your favorite main dishes.

title: Vegetarian Chili
description: This quick-cooking stovetop chili, chock full of vegetables and two types of beans will fit the bill when you're looking for a meatless dish.

title: Chili Cheese Quesadillas
description: Here is a quick and easy quesadilla recipe everyone will enjoy. Warm flour tortillas wrap around a filling of chili and Cheddar cheese and cook until golden. They are really good and perfect for those nights when you are in a pinch for time.

title: Caramelized Onion Tart
description: Slowly cooking sweet onions until golden creates a sophisticated filling between the flaky puff pastry crust and the smooth Grewyair and Parmesan cheese topping.

title: Roasted Tomato and Onion Tart
description: This meatless main dish features flaky puff pastry topped with roasted tomatoes and onion, and lots of shredded mozzarella cheese.  It's so good, it will have everyone craving vegetarian fare.

title: Broccoli & Cheese Stuffed Shells
description: Large pasta shells stuffed with creamy cheese and chopped broccoli are laced with seasoned tomato sauce and baked until piping hot.

title: Italian Frittata
description: Perfect for breakfast, brunch or a light supper, this baked Italian omelet sports fresh tomato, sawtayed onion and two kinds of cheese.

title: Mushroom & Goat Cheese Tart
description: Creamy goat cheese, sawtayed mushrooms, shallots and herbs fill a flaky puff pastry crust to make this elegant and savory tart.

title: Slow-Cooked Ratatouille with Penne
description: You won't miss the meat at all in this fabulous veggie and pasta dish that slow-cooks for hours so that the flavors really develop. You'll see how the zucchini, eggplant and peppers combine to make a mouthwatering pasta topper.

title: Roasted Vegetable Ratatouille
description: Here's an updated version of a classic ratatouille. Roasting the vegetables makes this version so much better than the original. And it's ready in less than one hour!

title: Chili Con Queso Bites
description: The Southwestern inspired flavors of Pace Picante Sauce combined with Cheddar cheese and chili powder create these delicious appetizers.

title: Nacho Cheese Bites
description: Bite-size appetizers are always perfect for entertaining these fit into both casual settings or more upscale cocktail parties. Serve with additional salsa for dipping.

title: Eggplant Tomato Gratin
description: Layers of eggplant, tomatoes, onion and cheese baked in a creamy sauce and topped with bread crumbs. Now you know this is going to be good!

title: Easy Spinach Stuffed Peppers
description: Fresh peppers are stuffed with a delicious combination featuring spinach, herb-seasoned stuffing, cream of mushroom soup and Parmesan cheese. Topped with mozzarella and baked to perfection, these stuffed peppers are simply irresistible!

title: Vegetable Minestrone Soup
description: Loaded with vegetables, this comforting and delicious minestrone is ready in only 40 minutes.

title: Farfalle Primavera
description: This easy pasta dish features saut_ed fresh vegetables simmered in a savory broth all tossed with farfalle pasta and Parmesan cheese. It's perfect for busy weeknights and is on the table in just 35 minutes!

title: Oven-Roasted Beet Soup with Orange Cream
description: Oven-roasted beets, parsnips and onion provide a flavorful base for this richly flavored soup that is ready to serve in less than one hour.

title: Creamy Southwest Tomato Soup
description: Sometimes the easiest recipes taste the best, and here's a great example. Salsa, tomato soup and milk blend together beautifully to make a delightful soup.

title: Range-Top Margherita-Style Pizza
description: Toasted whole wheat bread is seasoned with oregano and topped with tomatoes, melted mozzarella and fresh basil for an impromptu classic "pizza".

title: Pan-Grilled Veggie & Cheese Sandwiches
description: Favorite Mediterranean vegetables like eggplant, red pepper and portobello mushrooms mix with balsamic vinegar and mozzarella cheese to fill slices of whole wheat bread in this scrumptious grilled sandwich.

title: Eggplant Taleggio Panini
description: Here's a sandwich that really satisfies. Broiled eggplant, peppery arugula and Taleggio cheese in a multi-grain panini.  And it's ready in just 30 minutes!
